{"title_page": "M\u00e1rton B\u00e1der", "text_new": "{{short description|Hungarian basketball player}}\n{{Eastern name order|B\u00e1der M\u00e1rton}}\n{{Infobox basketball biography\n| name         = M\u00e1rton B\u00e1der\n| image        = \n| image_size   = \n| caption      = \n| position     = [[Power forward (basketball)|Power forward]] / [[Center (basketball)|Center]]\n| height_m     = 2.12\n| weight_kg    = 106\n| league       = \n| team         = \n| number       = \n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1980|09|23}}\n| birth_place  = [[Budapest]], Hungary\n| nationality  = Hungarian\n| draft_year   = 2002\n| career_start = 1998\n| career_end   = 2015\n| years1       = 1998\u20132000\n| team1        = [[Budapesti Honv\u00e9d (basketball)|Budapesti Honv\u00e9d]]\n| years2       = 2000\u20132002\n| team2        = [[Albacomp]]\n| years3       = 2002\u20132004\n| team3        = [[KK Krka|Krka]]\n| years4       = 2004\u20132005\n| team4        = [[KK Cibona|Cibona]]\n| years5       = 2006\n| team5        = [[B\u00e0squet Manresa|Ricoh Manresa]]\n| years6       = 2006\u20132007\n| team6        = Cibona\n| years7       = 2007\n| team7        = [[Panellinios B.C.|Panellinios]]\n| years8       = 2008\n| team8        = [[BK Prost\u011bjov|Prost\u011bjov]]\n| years9       = 2008\u20132009\n| team9        = [[BC Khimik|Khimik]]\n| years10      = 2009\n| team10       = [[KK Hemofarm|Hemofarm]]\n| years11      = 2010\u20132015\n| team11       = [[Szolnoki Olaj KK|Szolnoki Olaj]]\n| highlights   = \n* [[Premier A Slovenian Basketball League|Slovenian League]] (2003)\n* [[A-1 Liga|Croatian League]] (2007)\n* 4\u00d7 [[Nemzeti Bajnoks\u00e1g I/A (men's basketball)|Hungarian League]] (2011, 2012, 2014, 2015)\n* 4\u00d7 [[Magyar Kupa (men's basketball)|Hungarian Cup]] (2011, 2012, 2014, 2015)\n}}\n'''M\u00e1rton B\u00e1der''' (born September 23, 1980) is a Hungarian former professional [[basketball]] player. He is {{height|m=2.12}} tall, and played as a [[forward-center]].\n\nAfter starting his career in his homeland, B\u00e1der played in several countries including [[Slovenia]], [[Croatia]], [[Spain]], [[Greece]], [[Ukraine]] and [[Serbia]]. He was also a long-time member of the [[Hungary national basketball team|Hungarian national team]].\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of foreign basketball players in Serbia]]\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.aba-liga.com/player.php?id=285 M\u00e1rton B\u00e1der] at aba-liga.com\n* [http://www.acb.com/jugador.php?id=BAR M\u00e1rton B\u00e1der] at acb.com\n* [http://www.euroleague.net/competition/players/showplayer?pcode=BJJ M\u00e1rton B\u00e1der] at euroleague.net\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bader, Marton}}\n[[Category:1980 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Alba Feh\u00e9rv\u00e1r players]]\n[[Category:B\u00e0squet Manresa players]]\n[[Category:BC Khimik players]]\n[[Category:Centers (basketball)]]\n[[Category:Expatriate basketball people in Croatia]]\n[[Category:Expatriate basketball people in Greece]]\n[[Category:Hungarian expatriate basketball people in Serbia]]\n[[Category:Hungarian men's basketball players]]\n[[Category:Hungarian expatriate basketball people in Spain]]\n[[Category:KK Cibona players]]\n[[Category:KK Hemofarm players]]\n[[Category:KK Krka players]]\n[[Category:ABA League players]]\n[[Category:Liga ACB players]]\n[[Category:Panellinios B.C. players]]\n[[Category:Power forwards (basketball)]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Budapest]]\n[[Category:Szolnoki Olaj KK players]]\n[[Category:Hungarian expatriate sportspeople in Slovenia]]\n[[Category:Hungarian expatriate sportspeople in Croatia]]\n[[Category:Hungarian expatriate sportspeople in Greece]]\n[[Category:Hungarian expatriate sportspeople in the Czech Republic]]\n[[Category:Hungarian expatriate sportspeople in Ukraine]]\n\n\n{{Hungary-basketball-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Eastern name order|B\u00e1der M\u00e1rton}}\n{{Infobox basketball biography\n| name         = M\u00e1rton B\u00e1der\n| image        = \n| image_size   = \n|